               <p>MR. 
               <persName id="t18220703-25-person266">
                  JAMES 
                  BURBIDGE
               <interp inst="t18220703-25-person266" type="surname" value="BURBIDGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-25-person266" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220703-25-person266" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an <rs id="t18220703-25-viclabel126" type="occupation">ironmonger</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220703-25-victim265 t18220703-25-viclabel126"></join>, and live in Fleet-street. On Saturday, the 8th of June, about ten o'clock at night, I was a few doors on this side <placeName id="t18220703-25-crimeloc127">Temple-bar</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220703-25-crimeloc127" type="placeName" value="Temple-bar"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220703-25-crimeloc127" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220703-25-off124 t18220703-25-crimeloc127"></join>, coming home - I felt something at my pocket, and missed my handkerchief; upon turning round I saw the prisoner close at my heels - I believe he was in company with two other persons. I collared him, and the handkerchief dropped behind him; I said he had picked my pocket; he denied it - I took him to the watch-house. I picked it up.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220703-25-person267">
                  HENRY 
                  TALMAGE
